      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/design.md</file>
      <file>projects/INDEX.md (Maintenance Contract)</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Project-close test-diet gate" location=".claude/skills/test-diet/SKILL.md">
        Reconcile tests touched during project against ADR-038 17-ban classifier. Emit git rm / git mv commands; do NOT auto-execute.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Lessons-learned doc" location="notes/handoffs/lessons-learned.md">
        Honest retrospective: what went well, what hurt, what would change, spec gaps/errors. Reference R4 graduation closure + Action Engine R1 unblock.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Sibling worktree sync" location="notes/handoffs/r4-graduation-uat.md">
        On R7 close, R4 archive + Action Engine R1 resume past Phase 0 spike.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      R7 ran from 2026-06-28 to project-close. Key deliverables:
      - Dispatch reform: 3-layer → single-hop sprk_executortype Choice column
      - AiCompletionNodeExecutor built; closed R4 /narrate gap
      - Typed config schemas + PlaybookBuilder UI updates
      - 94 existing playbook nodes backfilled via owner manual review
      - Documentation cleanup (DELETE outdated, UPDATE current)
      - jps-* skill rewrites
      - chat-summarize migration to consumer-routing Path A.5
      - Playbook Library wired into 3 consumer surfaces

      Sibling unblocks at R7 close:
      - R4 (`spaarke-daily-update-service-r4`) archives (held since 2026-06-28 for /narrate)
      - Action Engine R1 (`ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1`) resumes past Phase 0 spike (held since Q14 2026-06-28)
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="101" status="not-started-but-required">R4 graduation UAT signed off PASS — gate to project close.</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>GitHub Issue #501 (portfolio Project Issue) — close on R7 wrap-up.</item>
      <item>Parent Epic #421 SPAARKE AI — remains open; R7 contributes to epic but does not close it.</item>
      <item>chat-routing-redesign-r1 follow-on owns docs/data-model/sprk_playbookconsumer.md + ai-architecture-consumer-routing.md updates (not R7).</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: STANDARD · 📋 REASON: wrap-up task (tag wrapup, doc + state updates only, no code change, no BFF modification) — Step 9.5 quality gates skipped per STANDARD rigor; HOWEVER /test-diet invocation at Step 2 is BINDING per CLAUDE.md §7 · Proceeding with Step 0...
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Load context">
      Read CLAUDE.md §7 (test-diet BINDING + Task Completion), spec.md, design.md, graduation-verification.md, r4-graduation-uat.md (confirm PASS sign-off present), test-diet SKILL.md, repo-cleanup SKILL.md.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Invoke /test-diet (BINDING per CLAUDE.md §7)">
      Invoke Skill tool with skill="test-diet" args="projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7".
      The skill:
      - Enumerates test files touched during R7 (git log start-commit..HEAD)
      - Classifies each test method as MAINTAIN / SCAFFOLDING / AMBIGUOUS per ADR-038 17 bans
      - Emits git rm / git mv commands (does NOT auto-execute)
      - Writes report at projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/test-diet-report.md
      If skipping: document reason in lessons-learned (HARD WARNING per CLAUDE.md §7).
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Apply test-diet recommendations">
      Review test-diet report. Apply DELETE/KEEP/MOVE per recommendations (reviewer judgment on AMBIGUOUS).
      Confirm tests still pass: dotnet test src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ (or full suite if scope warrants).
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Update README.md — flip Status to Complete">
      Edit projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/README.md:
      - Status: In Progress → Complete
      - Last Updated: bump to today's date
      - Changelog: add entry "R7 project closed. R4 graduation gate closed via FR-15. Action Engine R1 unblocked."
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Update CLAUDE.md — Phase: Complete">
      Edit projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/CLAUDE.md:
      - Phase: Complete
      - Current Task: none
      - Next Action: archived
      - Last Updated: today
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Update current-task.md — Status: none">
      Edit projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/current-task.md:
      - Status: none
      - Next action: /repo-cleanup
      - Active steps: cleared
      - Files in flight: cleared
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Write lessons-learned.md">
      Create projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/handoffs/lessons-learned.md with sections:
      - **What went well**: e.g., spec rigor + 33 FRs, sibling worktree coordination, manual per-node review at FR-19
      - **What hurt**: e.g., C# enum rename diff size, owner-checkpoint timing, Wave 4-9 ordering subtlety
      - **What would change next time**: e.g., earlier Wave 9 (chat-summarize) start, automated sync mechanism choice in Wave 1
      - **What spec missed or got wrong**: e.g., assumptions section items that hit reality differently
      - **R4 graduation closure**: reference notes/handoffs/r4-graduation-uat.md sign-off
      - **Action Engine R1 unblock**: reference Q14 hold release
      - **Test-diet outcome**: reference notes/test-diet-report.md (counts: N MAINTAIN, M SCAFFOLDING deleted, K AMBIGUOUS)
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Update projects/INDEX.md">
      Edit projects/INDEX.md:
      - Mark R7 row as Archived (per Maintenance Contract)
      - Or remove the row if the contract specifies removal for archived projects
      - Update 17-active-project counts and BFF/SpaarkeAi touch counts if affected
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Close GitHub Issue #501 + sibling-worktree sync">
      Run gh GraphQL/CLI to:
      - Set Issue #501 Status: Completed
      - Set Issue #501 Closed Date: today
      - Add closing comment citing notes/handoffs/lessons-learned.md + notes/handoffs/graduation-verification.md

      Sibling worktree sync (informational only — do NOT execute the sibling archives from here):
      - Document R4 cleared to archive (next action: `/devops-project-archive` on R4 worktree)
      - Document Action Engine R1 cleared to resume (next action: resume Phase 1 design)
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Optional — invoke /repo-cleanup">
      If owner approves, invoke Skill tool with skill="repo-cleanup" args="projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7". The skill validates structure compliance + removes ephemeral notes/* files per spec. If declined, mark as deferred to next maintenance cycle.
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="Verify acceptance">
      Re-read all 10 goal bullets. Confirm each satisfied:
      - test-diet invoked + report exists
      - README + CLAUDE + current-task flipped to Complete
      - lessons-learned.md written
      - INDEX.md updated
      - Issue #501 closed
      - Sibling unblocks documented
      - /repo-cleanup decision recorded
    </step>
    <step order="12" name="DO NOT commit — main session commits">
      Per task brief: do NOT commit. Main session commits the full wrap-up bundle at end with a single conventional message.
      Mark task 090-project-wrap-up status complete in TASK-INDEX (last row 🔲 → ✅).
      Project state: COMPLETE.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>Read (CLAUDE.md §7, spec, design, graduation-verification.md, r4-graduation-uat.md, test-diet + repo-cleanup SKILL files)</tool>
    <tool>Edit (README.md, CLAUDE.md, current-task.md, projects/INDEX.md)</tool>
    <tool>Write (notes/handoffs/lessons-learned.md)</tool>
    <tool>Skill (test-diet — BINDING per CLAUDE.md §7)</tool>
    <tool>Skill (repo-cleanup — optional)</tool>
    <tool>Bash (gh GraphQL/CLI for Issue #501 close, dotnet test post-diet to verify suite still green)</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
